events.name: Georgia State Panthers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron completed 15 of 16 passes for 166 yards and four touchdowns in the first half and No. 1 Alabama rolled to a 45-3 victory over Georgia State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCarron sharp as Bama cruises

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Marcus Mariota threw five touchdown passes and ran for two scores as No. 2 Oregon brushed off some early trickery to rout Colorado 57-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mariota's 7 TDs lift No. 2 Oregon

events.name: Clemson Tigers at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd kept his Heisman Trophy aspirations intact, throwing for 455 yards and five touchdowns in three quarters of work, and No. 3 Clemson beat Syracuse 49-14 on Saturday to spoil the Orange's Atlantic Coast Conference debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 3 Clemson rolls at Syracuse

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Carlos Hyde ran for a career-high 168 yards and three touchdowns, and No. 4 Ohio State rallied to beat No. 16 Northwestern 40-30 Saturday night and extend the nation's longest win streak to 18 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Ohio State storms back

events.name: Washington Huskies at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Ty Montgomery had 290 all-purpose yards and two touchdowns, and fifth-ranked Stanford held on to beat No. 15 Washington 31-28 on Saturday night in a matchup of unbeaten Pac-12 North teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford holds on vs. Washington

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: Marshall Morgan kicked a 42-yard field goal in overtime after No. 6 Georgia scored a tying touchdown with 5 seconds left in regulation as the Bulldogs overcame numerous injuries and beat Tennessee 34-31 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia escapes Vols in OT

events.name: Louisville Cardinals at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Teddy Bridgewater threw for 348 yards and two touchdowns to keep No. 7 Louisville undefeated with a 30-7 win over winless Temple on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridgewater, Louisville rout winless Temple

events.name: Maryland Terrapins at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Eighth-ranked Florida State stayed undefeated in Atlantic Coast Conference play with a 63-0 victory over No. 25 Maryland on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 8 FSU demolishes Maryland 63-0

events.name: LSU Tigers at Mississippi State Bulldogs

headlines.description: Zach Mettenberger threw for 340 yards and two touchdowns, Odell Beckham Jr. had 179 yards receiving and two TDs, and No. 10 LSU pushed past Mississippi State 59-26 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 10 LSU pulls away to beat Mississippi St.

events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Brennan Clay broke a 76-yard touchdown run late in the fourth quarter and No. 11 Oklahoma held off TCU 20-17 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clay helps No. 11 Oklahoma hold off TCU

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Connor Shaw passed for a touchdown and ran for another as No. 13 South Carolina, playing without injured defensive end Jadeveon Clowney, held off a Kentucky comeback for a 35-28 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 13 South Carolina wins minus Clowney

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Stephen Morris threw for three touchdowns, Duke Johnson rushed for 184 yards and No. 14 Miami remained unbeaten after shaking off a problematic first quarter to beat Georgia Tech 45-30 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami shakes off slow start, tops Ga. Tech

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Bryce Petty threw for 347 yards with two touchdowns and had one of Baylor's eight rushing TDs as No. 17 Bears kept up their big-scoring ways in the Big 12, beating West Virginia 73-42 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor's 864 total yards break Big 12 record

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Solomon Patton turned two short receptions into touchdowns, helping No. 18 Florida beat Arkansas 30-10 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Patton, No. 18 Florida cruise past Arkansas

events.name: Minnesota Golden Gophers at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Devin Gardner threw a 24-yard, go-ahead touchdown pass to Devin Funchess late in the first half and No. 19 Michigan pulled away to rout Minnesota 42-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Michigan rumbles past coach-less Minnesota

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Freshman sensation Baker Mayfield passed for 368 yards but was helped off the field with an apparent leg injury in the third quarter of No. 20 Texas Tech's 54-16 victory over Kansas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield hurt in Tech win

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: J.W. Walsh found Charlie Moore for a 6-yard touchdown pass with 4:16 left in the fourth quarter to help No. 21 Oklahoma State rally for a 33-29 win over Kansas State.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 21 Cowboys use late TD to KO K-State

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Tommy Rees threw for 279 yards and three touchdowns, and Notre Dame made it 5 for 5 in the traveling Shamrock Series with a 37-34 victory against No. 22 Arizona State on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rees-led Irish knock off No. 22 Arizona St.

events.name: Fresno State Bulldogs at Idaho Vandals

headlines.description: Derek Carr threw five touchdown passes as No. 23 Fresno State pounded Idaho 61-14 on Saturday, scoring at least 40 points for the fifth time this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Carr helps Fresno St. again tops 40 points

events.name: Ole Miss Rebels at Auburn Tigers

headlines.description: Nick Marshall ran for 140 yards and two touchdowns, Robenson Therezie scored on a 78-yard interception return and Auburn held off No. 24 Mississippi 30-22 on Saturday night for its first win over a Top 25 team in two years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Auburn knocks off Ole Miss behind Marshall

events.name: Air Force Falcons at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Keenan Reynolds ran for 126 yards and three touchdowns, and Navy used a strong second half to beat Air Force28-10 Saturday in a game that survived the restrictions of the U.S. government shutdown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Navy tops Air Force amid government shutdown

headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana finds way to finally beat Penn State

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Ameer Abdullah ran for a career-high 225 yards and two touchdowns and Nebraska's maligned defense was much improved in a 39-19 victory over Illinois on Saturday.
